biography: Reina Staley hails from the land of the endless night, born into a family of Artic Researchers who thought it would be a great idea to have a child born at the South Pole.  Having no real citizenship, Reina has spent her live hopping from country to country living out the maximum time on 124 visas.  Her favorite country so far was Paraguay and their native jelly bean industry.  In her spare time she enjoys writing policies on cloud computing and keeping all yo data on lock down.
